Light-skinned people are most susceptible
to skin cancers because they have to make

00:02:47.835 --> 00:02:50.355
up for not having the melanin in the first
place.

00:02:50.355 --> 00:02:55.595
Darker skinned people scatter more of the
UV rays naturally, and therefore have significantly

00:02:55.595 --> 00:02:59.465
lower incidences of skin cancer, according
to the CDC[a].

00:02:59.465 --> 00:03:03.625
Obviously, you can use sunscreen, which contains
organic and inorganic chemicals to block the

00:03:03.625 --> 00:03:05.105
UV rays that cause cancers.

00:03:05.105 --> 00:03:08.205
